---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Logo Designer Red Flags | Logo Brief Guide"
  description="Watch for these common warning signs before you hire a logo designer or approve a package."
  pathname="/logo-designer-red-flags/"
>
  <section class="prose">
    <p class="eyebrow">Supporting page</p>
    <h1>Logo designer red flags</h1>
    <p>
      The goal is not paranoia. The goal is to avoid preventable mistakes before
      money changes hands.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="card-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <h2>Vague deliverables</h2>
        <p>No clear file list, no clarity on revisions, no explanation of what you actually receive.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h2>Portfolio mismatch</h2>
        <p>Nice-looking samples, but nothing that resembles the type of business or style you need.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h2>Too-good promises</h2>
        <p>Huge claims, no process, and unrealistic speed can be signs of low-effort work.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h2>No questions asked</h2>
        <p>Good designers usually need context. If no one asks about your business, audience, or usage, that is a warning sign.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Best defense</h2>
      <p>
        Start with a clear brief and a clear deliverables list. Buyers who do that
        usually avoid the worst outcomes.
      </p>
      <p><a class="button" href="/logo-brief-template/">Start with the brief template</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
